#: epilogues.tra:4001
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Aerie continued adventuring after years after leaving <CHARNAME>'s company, "
#| "often traveling with a larger group but sometimes striking out on her own to"
#| " use her considerable power to fight against slavery in the Realms.  Her "
#| "compassion grew tainted by revenge, however; revenge for what had been taken"
#| " from her when she was in chains and could never be restored.  She might "
#| "have lost herself to her vengeance entirely had fortune not smiled upon her."
#| "  The tale goes that Aerie, filled with a righteous fury, destroyed a slaver"
#| " enclave in the northern hills of Cormyr single-handedly.  She was surprised"
#| " to find a group of avariel elves that had been held captive there and "
#| "quickly freed them, and was in turn invited to return to her long-lost home "
#| "of Faenya-Dail.  She learned much while she was there.  Most importantly, "
#| "she learned she was no longer truly one of avariel, and let go forever of "
#| "the wings that she had lost. Faenya-Dail was no longer her home, and it was "
#| "with mixed emotions that she bid it farewell.  It is said that Aerie "
#| "eventually became a high priestess in Understone, a gnomish village her "
#| "mentor Quayle had sometimes spoken of.  He had been her true family, and it "
#| "was among his people that she finally found happiness and the family she had"
#| " always longed for.  It was also said that Aerie prayed for her old friend, "
#| "<CHARNAME>, each night as the stars revealed themselves in the sky above.  "
#| "She sincerely hoped her friend had been fortunate enough to find the peace "
#| "that she had... for without <CHARNAME>, it would never have been possible."
msgid ""
"Aerie continued adventuring after years after leaving <CHARNAME>'s company, "
"often traveling with a larger group but sometimes striking out on her own to"
" use her considerable power to fight against slavery in the Realms. Her "
"compassion grew tainted by revenge, however, revenge for what had been taken"
" from her when she was in chains and could never be restored. She might have"
" lost herself to her vengeance entirely had fortune not smiled upon her. The"
" tale goes that Aerie, filled with a righteous fury, destroyed a slaver "
"enclave in the northern hills of Cormyr single-handedly. She was surprised "
"to find a group of avariel elves that had been held captive there and "
"quickly freed them, and was in turn invited to return to her long-lost home "
"of Faenya-Dail. She learned much while she was there. Most importantly, she "
"learned she was no longer truly one of avariel, and let go forever of the "
"wings that she had lost. Faenya-Dail was no longer her home, and it was with"
" mixed emotions that she bid it farewell. It is said that Aerie eventually "
"became a high priestess in Understone, a gnomish village her mentor Quayle "
"had sometimes spoken of. He had been her true family, and it was among his "
"people that she finally found happiness and the family she had always longed"
" for. It was also said that Aerie prayed for her old friend, <CHARNAME>, "
"each night as the stars revealed themselves in the sky above. She sincerely "
"hoped her friend had been fortunate enough to find the peace that she had..."
" for without <CHARNAME>, it would never have been possible."
msgstr ""
"Aerie continua sa vie aventureuse après avoir quitté <CHARNAME>, se posant "
"comme une féroce adversaire de toute forme d'esclavage. Sa compassion "
"commença à être empreinte de vengeance cependant, de la vengeance pour ce "
"qui lui avait été pris lorsqu'elle était enchaînée et ne lui serait jamais "
"rendu. Elle aurait pu perdre la raison si la fortune ne lui avait pas souri."
" Les histoires disent qu'Aerie, pleine de rage, détruisit une enclave "
"d'esclavagistes dans les collines au nord du Cormyr à elle seule. Elle fut "
"surprise d'y trouver un groupe d'Avariels qui étaient retenus prisonniers et"
" les libéra en vitesse. Ils la persuadèrent de rejoindre Faenya-Dail, sa "
"patrie, où elle apprit beaucoup, notamment qu'elle ne serait jamais plus une"
" Avariel. Elle cessa donc de se lamenter et de tenter de récupérer ses "
"ailes, sachant que c'était désormais inutile. Faenya-Dail n'était plus son "
"foyer, et ce fut troublée qu'elle en partit pour toujours. Il est dit "
"qu'Aerie finit par devenir une grande prêtresse à Pierrebasse, un village "
"gnome dont son tuteur Quayle lui avait quelquefois parlé. Il avait été sa "
"seule vraie famille, et c'est parmi son peuple qu'elle trouva finalement la "
"joie et la famille qu'elle avait souhaité. Il est aussi dit qu'Aerie priait "
"pour son ancien ami, <CHARNAME>, chaque nuit alors que les étoiles "
"apparaissaient dans le ciel. Elle espérait sincèrement que son ami ait eu la"
" chance de trouver la paix qu'elle avait trouvée... grâce à lui."

#: epilogues.tra:4002
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Aerie and <CHARNAME> would prove inseparable, continuing their adventuring "
#| "for many years into the future.  Aerie's zest for travel brought the pair "
#| "over much of FaerÃ»n and even further.  Their young son was always in tow, "
#| "making <CHARNAME> smile with his wide-eyed awe at the wonders of the world."
#| "  Eventually the pair would settle, subsequently giving birth to a beautiful"
#| " daughter that was the second joy of their lives.  Only rarely would trouble"
#| " cause <CHARNAME> and Aerie to bring their great power to bear against the "
#| "evil of the world, though the tales of their battles would become legendary."
#| "  Their later years would hold one last great trek, as Aerie still felt a "
#| "sadness from her time of enslavement and the loss of her wings.  Together "
#| "she and <CHARNAME> sought the Avariel of Faenya-Dail, the winged elves she "
#| "was stolen from so long ago.  They discovered not only her people, but "
#| "loving parents that had spent years searching for their lost child.  Aerie "
#| "had finally found her family.  With no more mystery or confusion to cloud "
#| "their lives, it was there, among the clouds, that Aerie and <CHARNAME> would"
#| " finally be married.  Their union, it is said, was blessed by the presence "
#| "of Aerdrie Faenya and Baervan Wildwanderer both.  As for the children of "
#| "<CHARNAME> and Aerie, tutored by two of the Realm's most powerful beings, "
#| "their own destiny would be a tale to rival their father's..."
msgid ""
"Aerie and <CHARNAME> would prove inseparable, continuing their adventuring "
"for many years into the future. Aerie's zest for travel brought the pair "
"over much of Faerun and even further. Their young son was always in tow, "
"making <CHARNAME> smile with his wide-eyed awe at the wonders of the world. "
"Eventually the pair would settle, subsequently giving birth to a beautiful "
"daughter that was the second joy of their lives. Only rarely would trouble "
"cause <CHARNAME> and Aerie to bring their great power to bear against the "
"evil of the world, though the tales of their battles would become legendary."
" Their later years would hold one last great trek, as Aerie still felt a "
"sadness from her time of enslavement and the loss of her wings. Together she"
" and <CHARNAME> sought the Avariel of Faenya-Dail, the winged elves she was "
"stolen from so long ago. They discovered not only her people, but loving "
"parents that had spent years searching for their lost child. Aerie had "
"finally found her family. With no more mystery or confusion to cloud their "
"lives, it was there, among the clouds, that Aerie and <CHARNAME> would "
"finally be married. Their union, it is said, was blessed by the presence of "
"Aerdrie Faenya and Baervan Wildwanderer both. As for the children of "
"<CHARNAME> and Aerie, tutored by two of the Realm's most powerful beings, "
"their own destiny would be a tale to rival their father's..."
msgstr ""
"Aerie et <CHARNAME> prouvèrent qu'ils étaient inséparables, continuant leurs"
" aventures plusieurs années encore. L'envie de voyage d'Aerie emmena le "
"couple à travers tout Féerune, voire plus loin. Leur jeune fils les "
"accompagnait toujours, faisant sourire <CHARNAME> à chaque fois qu'il "
"écarquillait ses yeux sur les merveilles du monde. Finalement le couple "
"s'établit, donnant naissance à une fille qui devint la seconde joie de leurs"
" vies. Rarement <CHARNAME> et Aerie furent amenés à quitter leur retraite "
"pour utiliser leurs grands pouvoirs contre le mal, bien que les récits de "
"leurs combats devinrent légendaires. Les années suivantes les amenèrent à "
"entreprendre un long voyage, alors qu'Aerie ressentait de la tristesse en se"
" rappelant ses années d'esclavage et la perte de ses ailes. Elle et "
"<CHARNAME> cherchèrent les Avariels de Faenya-Dail, les elfes ailés à qui "
"elle avait été enlevée il y a bien longtemps. Ils découvrirent non seulement"
" son peuple, mais aussi des parents aimants qui avaient passés des années à "
"chercher leur enfant perdue. Aerie avait finalement trouvé sa famille. Sans "
"plus aucun mystère ou confusion dans leurs vies, ce fût ici, parmi les "
"nuages, qu'Aerie et <CHARNAME> se marièrent enfin. Leur union, dit-on, fut "
"bénie par la présence d'Aerdrie Faenya et Baervan Ermiterrant. Concernant "
"les enfants de <CHARNAME> et d'Aerie, instruits par deux des plus puissants "
"héros des Royaumes, leur futur est destiné à être une légende rivalisant "
"avec celle de leur père..."

#: epilogues.tra:4003
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Eventually parting ways with his companions, Anomen would enter the "
#| "hierarchy of Helm's church, over time rising to the rank of High Watcher.  "
#| "He remained restless and dissatisfied, remembering his days adventuring with"
#| " <CHARNAME>...and though many friends would urge him otherwise, Anomen never"
#| " felt that the church was his true home.  He remained in his position for a "
#| "year until finally he could bear it no more.  He left active duty in the "
#| "church and, for a time, wandered the new land of Maztica as a missionary.  "
#| "Anomen remained a troubled soul, still never content even though his prowess"
#| " earned him great respect from the new friends he encountered.  When the "
#| "powerful evil priest Yamash summoned a horde of demons in an effort to rid "
#| "Maztica of all life, Anomen would at last find his purpose.  He alone was "
#| "responsible for organizing the tattered remnants of the Amnish soldiers and "
#| "local Mazticans into a united army that stood against the dark priest.  In "
#| "the great battle that followed, Anomen was seen plainly by all to plunge "
#| "into combat single-handedly against Yamash.  He did not have <CHARNAME> or "
#| "other companions beside him: alone he stood against the tide of evil, and "
#| "for once he was not found wanting.  He was last seen from afar, shedding "
#| "tears of joy as he engaged Yamash and shouted out to Helm while chanelling a"
#| " blinding flash of power.  When it cleared, both the priest and Anomen were "
#| "gone.  The battle was won and Maztica was saved.  Anomen would forever after"
#| " be regarded as a hero, inspiring the creation of a protective order of "
#| "knights in his name.  A new order for a new land."
msgid ""
"Eventually parting ways with his companions, Anomen would enter the "
"hierarchy of Helm's church, over time rising to the rank of High Watcher. He"
" remained restless and dissatisfied, remembering his days adventuring with "
"<CHARNAME>...and though many friends would urge him otherwise, Anomen never "
"felt that the church was his true home. He remained in his position for a "
"year until finally he could bear it no more. He left active duty in the "
"church and, for a time, wandered the new land of Maztica as a missionary. "
"Anomen remained a troubled soul, still never content even though his prowess"
" earned him great respect from the new friends he encountered. When the "
"powerful evil priest Yamash summoned a horde of demons in an effort to rid "
"Maztica of all life, Anomen would at last find his purpose. He alone was "
"responsible for organizing the tattered remnants of the Amnish soldiers and "
"local Mazticans into a united army that stood against the dark priest. In "
"the great battle that followed, Anomen was seen plainly by all to plunge "
"into combat single-handedly against Yamash. He did not have <CHARNAME> or "
"other companions beside him: alone he stood against the tide of evil, and "
"for once he was not found wanting. He was last seen from afar, shedding "
"tears of joy as he engaged Yamash and shouted out to Helm while chanelling a"
" blinding flash of power. When it cleared, both the priest and Anomen were "
"gone. The battle was won and Maztica was saved. Anomen would forever after "
"be regarded as a hero, inspiring the creation of a protective order of "
"knights in his name. A new order for a new land."
msgstr ""
"Finissant par se séparer de ses compagnons, Anomen entra dans la hiérarchie "
"de l'église de Helm, atteignant avec le temps le rang de Grand Vigilant. Il "
"resta infatigable et insatisfait, se rappelant des mois passé aux côtés de "
"<CHARNAME>... et bien que de nombreux amis lui dirent le contraire, Anomen "
"ne sentit jamais que l'église était son vrai foyer. Il resta à ce poste un "
"an et finalement ne put le supporter davantage. Il laissa son travail à "
"l'église et, pour un temps, erra dans la contrée de Maztica en tant que "
"missionnaire.  Anomen resta un esprit troublé, ne trouvant jamais "
"satisfaction bien que ses prouesses lui aient valu le respect des nouveaux "
"compagnons qu'il rencontrât. Quand le puissant et maléfique prêtre Yamash "
"invoqua une horde de Démons pour tenter de détruire toute vie sur Maztica, "
"Anomen trouva enfin sa voie. Seul, il organisa quelques soldats Amniens et "
"les habitants de Maztica en une armée unie qui s'opposa au sombre prêtre. "
"Lors du grand combat qui suivit, Anomen fût vu par tous en train de se "
"battre seul face à Yamash. Il n'avait pas <CHARNAME> ou d'autres compagnons "
"à ses côtés : seul il s'opposa au mal, et avait enfin trouvé ce qu'il "
"cherchait. Il fût aperçu pour la dernière fois de loin, versant des larmes "
"de joie tandis qu'il affrontait Yamash et priait Helm en concentrant une "
"lumière aveuglante de puissance. Lorsque cette lumière se dissipa, aussi "
"bien Anomen que le prêtre avaient disparu. Le combat fût gagné et Maztica "
"sauvée. Anomen fût toujours regardé comme un héros, inspirant la création "
"d'un ordre de chevaliers protecteurs en son nom. Un nouvel ordre pour un "
"nouveau pays."

#: epilogues.tra:4004
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Anomen and <CHARNAME> continued adventuring until they were known as heroes "
#| "almost everywhere they went.  Many were the grand tales of the Shining "
#| "Knight and his utter devotion to his great lady.  <CHARNAME>'s past as the "
#| "terrible Bhaalspawn was forgotten forever as new deeds replaced old and a "
#| "legacy was created that far outstripped anything granted by godly blood.  So"
#| " prolific were their careers that the proposed date of their wedding kept "
#| "getting moved back, either due to impending crisis or some lucrative "
#| "adventure that one or the other would insist on investigating. Finally a "
#| "date approached that both <CHARNAME> and her beloved were determined to "
#| "keep, and the much heralded event drew heroes and dignitaries from across "
#| "FaerÃ»n. The couple had touched the lives of many, and those people arrived "
#| "in droves to watch Elminster himself unite the two in one of the grandest "
#| "ceremonies the city of Baldur's Gate had ever seen. Anomen and <CHARNAME> "
#| "retired from public life shortly after the celebrated birth of their "
#| "daughter, although if tales be true, their adventures never truly ended.  "
#| "Anomen would rise high in the hierarchy of his church, and <CHARNAME> would "
#| "continue to be the center of strange events throughout their lives.  So, "
#| "too, would their daughter, tutored by two of the greatest heroes in the "
#| "Realms, forge a legend to rival that of her mother's.  That, however, is "
#| "another story completely..."
msgid ""
"Anomen and <CHARNAME> continued adventuring until they were known as heroes "
"almost everywhere they went. Many were the grand tales of the Shining Knight"
" and his utter devotion to his great lady. <CHARNAME>'s past as the terrible"
" Bhaalspawn was forgotten forever as new deeds replaced old and a legacy was"
" created that far outstripped anything granted by godly blood. So prolific "
"were their careers that the proposed date of their wedding kept getting "
"moved back, either due to impending crisis or some lucrative adventure that "
"one or the other would insist on investigating. Finally a date approached "
"that both <CHARNAME> and her beloved were determined to keep, and the much "
"heralded event drew heroes and dignitaries from across Faerun. The couple "
"had touched the lives of many, and those people arrived in droves to watch "
"Elminster himself unite the two in one of the grandest ceremonies the city "
"of Baldur's Gate had ever seen. Anomen and <CHARNAME> retired from public "
"life shortly after the celebrated birth of their daughter, although if tales"
" be true, their adventures never truly ended. Anomen would rise high in the "
"hierarchy of his church, and <CHARNAME> would continue to be the center of "
"strange events throughout their lives. So, too, would their daughter, "
"tutored by two of the greatest heroes in the Realms, forge a legend to rival"
" that of her mother's. That, however, is another story completely..."
msgstr ""
"Anomen et <CHARNAME> continuèrent l'aventure jusqu'à ce qu'ils soient "
"considérés comme des héros à peu près partout où ils allaient. Nombres "
"étaient les histoires sur le Chevalier Etincelant et sa dévotion à sa Dame. "
"Le passé de <CHARNAME> en tant qu'Enfant de Bhaal fût oublié à jamais tandis"
" que de nouveaux faits remplaçaient les anciens et ils en tirèrent une "
"gloire dépassant tout ce que pouvait apporter un sang divin. Leurs actions "
"furent si prolifiques que le jour fixé de leur mariage, ils partirent en "
"mission chacun de leur côté, à propos d'une quelconque crise ou aventure sur"
" laquelle ils insistaient de pouvoir enquêter. Une date fut finalement "
"fixée, que <CHARNAME> et Anomen respectèrent. Les plus grands héros et les "
"plus grandes figures de Féérune se déplacèrent pour assister à la cérémonie."
" Tous connaissaient les deux héros, au moins de renom, et tous voulaient "
"voir Elminster en personne unir ces deux êtres d'exception au cours de ce "
"qui fut sans doute la plus belle cérémonie de toute l'histoire de la Porte "
"de Baldur. Anomen et <CHARNAME> se retirèrent de la vie publique peu de "
"temps après la naissance de leur fille, bien que si les histoires sont "
"vraies, leurs aventures ne connurent jamais vraiment de fin. Anomen se "
"serait élevé très haut dans la hiérarchie de son église, et <CHARNAME> "
"aurait continué à être le centre d'événements étranges tout le long de leur "
"vie. Bientôt également, leur fille, élevée par deux des plus grand héros des"
" Royaumes, se forgerait une légende capable de rivaliser avec celle de sa "
"mère. Mais ceci est une autre histoire..."

