#| msgid ""
#| "Upon parting ways with <CHARNAME>, the reborn Sarevok proved as good as his word.  He returned to the lands he once knew, far more powerful now than he was even before.  Old enemies were startled by his visits, but never for long, and it was not even months later that Sarevok would start a reign of terror in Baldur's Gate that would place him completely in charge of the city.  Resistance was crushed as Sarevok began raising an army for conquest in his own name.  If he could not have the divine power of his father, he would have enough earthly power to satiate his appetite.  Sarevok partook of women as he pleased as his name became a bitter epithet on the tongue of every citizen of the Sword Coast.\n"
#| "The first victims of his terrible army fell easily, and Sarevok's power grew.  The warrior was maddened, however, to find that the victories gave him no thrill.  The power tasted as ashes, though Sarevok tried many times to drive himself into a frenzy of delight at his achievements.  In the end, his throne grew heavy, and it was with dread acceptance that he greeted the arrival of the inevitable heroes to displace him not a year after his return.\n"
#| "Sarevok fled into the night, abandoning Baldur's Gate and his dreams of power both.  He became a man haunted by his second chance, hunted by a former life that never was and a possible life that never could be.  Without a destiny and or a true soul of his own, he wandered the Realms... sometimes he brought terror and sometimes he brought nothing but his tired heart, and before long he was gone forever.  Some say that he found his purpose in the great desert, forging a kingdom to last an age.  Some say he traveled to the planes, launching a campaign against the great Mount Celestia.  The truth is unknown, though the tales still persist."
msgid ""
"Upon parting ways with <CHARNAME>, the reborn Sarevok proved as good as his word. He returned to the lands he once knew, far more powerful now than he was even before. Old enemies were startled by his visits, but never for long, and it was not even months later that Sarevok would start a reign of terror in Baldur's Gate that would place him completely in charge of the city. Resistance was crushed as Sarevok began raising an army for conquest in his own name. If he could not have the divine power of his father, he would have enough earthly power to satiate his appetite. Sarevok partook of women as he pleased as his name became a bitter epithet on the tongue of every citizen of the Sword Coast.\n"
"The first victims of his terrible army fell easily, and Sarevok's power grew. The warrior was maddened, however, to find that the victories gave him no thrill. The power tasted as ashes, though Sarevok tried many times to drive himself into a frenzy of delight at his achievements. In the end, his throne grew heavy, and it was with dread acceptance that he greeted the arrival of the inevitable heroes to displace him not a year after his return.\n"
"Sarevok fled into the night, abandoning Baldur's Gate and his dreams of power both. He became a man haunted by his second chance, hunted by a former life that never was and a possible life that never could be. Without a destiny and or a true soul of his own, he wandered the Realms... sometimes he brought terror and sometimes he brought nothing but his tired heart, and before long he was gone forever. Some say that he found his purpose in the great desert, forging a kingdom to last an age. Some say he traveled to the planes, launching a campaign against the great Mount Celestia. The truth is unknown, though the tales still persist."
msgstr ""
"Après s'être séparé de <CHARNAME>, le Sarevok revenu de la tombe se montra "
"fidèle à sa réputation. Il retourna dans les contrées qu'il connaissait, "
"bien plus puissant qu'il ne l'avait jamais été. Ses anciens ennemis furent "
"surpris par sa venue, mais jamais très longtemps, et c'est quelques mois "
"plus tard que Sarevok monta un règne de terreur à la Porte de Baldur qui le "
"placerait entièrement en charge de la cité. La résistance fût écrasée tandis"
" que Sarevok commençait à lever une armée pour mener des conquêtes en son "
"nom. S'il n'avait plus le pouvoir divin de son père, il avait toujours "
"suffisamment de force pour satisfaire sa soif de pouvoir. Sarevok se servait"
" des femmes comme il le voulait alors que son nom devenait une malédiction "
"dans la bouche des citoyens de la Côte des Epées. Les premières victimes de "
"son armée tombèrent aisément, et le pouvoir de Sarevok grandit. Le guerrier "
"était furieux cependant de ne tirer aucun plaisir de ses victoires. Le "
"pouvoir avait le goût de cendres, bien que Sarevok tenta à maintes reprises "
"de se forcer à ressentir de la joie de ses conquêtes. Finalement son trône "
"devint lourd à porter, et ce fût avec une sombre résignation qu'il guetta "
"l'arrivée inévitable de héros venus le chasser un an après. Sarevok fuit "
"dans la nuit, abandonnant la Porte de Baldur et ses rêves de pouvoirs. Il "
"devint un homme hanté par sa seconde chance, pourchassé par une ancienne vie"
" qui n'avait jamais été et par une vie possible qui ne pourrait être. Sans "
"destinée ou véritable âme, il erra à travers les Royaumes... apportant "
"quelquefois la terreur, et d'autres fois ne traînant que son coeur las... et"
" finalement il disparût pour de bon. Certains disent qu'il trouva le sens de"
" sa vie dans le Grand Désert, forgeant un royaume qui durerait longtemps. "
"D'autres prétendent qu'il aurait traversé les plans, lançant une campagne "
"contre le Grand Mont Celestia. La vérité reste inconnue, bien que les "
"légendes persistent."

